For this data science project, a Dell XPS 13 (see \ref{fig:hardware}) is used with Manjaro Linux operating system.\\
\begin{figure}[ht!]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{Figures/hardware}
    \decoRule
    \caption[Used hardware]{Used hardware}
    \label{fig:hardware}
\end{figure}

\noindent
The analysis software is Jupyter Notebook \cite{jupyter} with Python \cite{python}. It is planned to move the model-specific code into an extra file for a better overview in the Notebook. It is not necessary to use any online resources.\\

\noindent
The following python modules will be used:\\

\begin{table}[ht!]
    \caption{Used python modules}
    \label{tab:python_modules}
    \begin{center}
        \begin{tabular}{|l|r|}
             \hline
             \textbf{Modul name} & \textbf{Version number} \\ \hline
             pandas {\small \cite{pandas}} & 1.4.4 \\ \hline
             numpy {\small \cite{numpy}} & 1.23.3 \\ \hline
             matplotlib {\small \cite{matplotlib}} & 3.5.2 \\ \hline
             scikit-learn {\small \cite{sklearn}} & 1.1.2 \\ \hline
             tensorflow {\small \cite{tensorflow}} & 2.11.0-dev20220927 \\ \hline
        \end{tabular}
    \end{center}
\end{table}

\noindent
It is intended to use the linear regression model from scikit-learn and a neural network with tensorflow for the analysis.
